# Detect-Dependencies Usability Issues

Found by running `detect-dependencies` on real third-party projects (jsoup, gson, commons-lang, commons-collections, commons-io, commons-text, spring-petclinic, javaparser).

## Re-Test Results (May 7, 2026 — after fixes)

| # | Issue | Status | Notes |
|---|-------|--------|-------|
| 1 | Plugin prefix not resolved | **OPEN** | Maven limitation — requires settings.xml `<pluginGroup>` or full GAV |
| 2 | Multi-module skips children | **FIXED** ✓ | Now iterates over all reactor modules |
| 3 | Silent failure (RAT/checkstyle) | **FIXED** ✓ | commons-io now discovers 248 tests (was 0) |
| 4 | JUnit 4 silent no-op | **FIXED** ✓ | Now BUILD FAILURE with actionable dependency snippet |
| 5 | False "Unknown property" warnings | **FIXED** ✓ | No more warnings for `testorder.detect.*` |
| 6 | "Loaded state" + "No prior data" | **FIXED** ✓ | Now says "(N with test outcomes)" or "(none with usable test outcomes)" |
| 7 | Empty report — no metadata | **FIXED** ✓ | Full metadata section in JSON report |
| 8 | No progress indicator | **OPEN** | No periodic updates during detection |
| 9 | Invalid algorithm silently falls back | **FIXED** ✓ | Now fails fast listing valid options |
| 10 | Contradictory dual warnings | **FIXED** ✓ | Resolved by fix to #5 + #9 |
| 11 | help doesn't mention detect-deps | **FIXED** ✓ | Now listed in help with examples |
| 12 | No detect properties in help | **FIXED** ✓ | Full "Detection properties" section added |
| 13 | Stale lock uses JUL format | **UNTESTED** | No stale lock triggered in re-test |
| 14 | Subprocess output discarded | **FIXED** ✓ | Now shows "Last output lines:" on failure |
| 15 | "No test classes" misleading | **IMPROVED** | Now shows specific causes list on failure |
| 16 | Time budget exceeded | **OPEN** | 30s budget → 52s actual (single run can exceed) |
| 17 | No graceful Ctrl+C shutdown | **UNTESTED** | |
